%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Broken%20whiter%20ceramic%20piggy%20bank%20in%20pieces%20on%20red%20surface%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F641e060ec60a3d00184eee00%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223509%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EPM%20Images%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EVanguard%20data%20shows%20more%20Americans%20are%20withdrawing%20retirement%20savings%20early%20in%202024.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBoth%20hardship%20and%20nonhardship%20distributions%20are%20rising.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFinancial%20pros%20suggest%20building%20savings%20buffers%20and%20borrowing%20against%20accounts%20to%20avoid%20penalties.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20are%20increasingly%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fretirement-planning%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etheir%20401(k)s%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20emergency%20funds.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20Vanguard%20shared%20with%20Business%20Insider%20highlights%20the%20trend%2C%20and%20it's%20something%20the%20financial%20advisors%20say%20people%20in%20most%20circumstances%20should%20try%20to%20steer%20clear%20of%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reason.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20shows%20that%204.8%25%20of%20those%20with%20401(k)%20accounts%20took%20hardship%20distributions%20in%202024%2C%20continuing%20an%20upward%20trend%20over%20the%20last%20four%20years.%20Nonhardship%20withdrawals%20are%20also%20rising%2C%20with%204.5%25%20of%20account%20holders%20taking%20money%20out%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222058%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22401(k)%20withdrawals%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68891cb33d5881a51c1e31d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221180%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEarly%20401(k)%20withdrawals%20are%20becoming%20more%20common.%3Cp%3EVanguard%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20nonhardship%20distributions%20are%20subject%20to%20a%2010%25%20penalty%20when%20taken%20before%2059%20and%20a%20half%20years%20old.%20Qualifying%20hardship%20distributions%20%E2%80%94%20which%20include%20circumstances%20like%20medical%2C%20funeral%2C%20tuition%2C%20and%20some%20housing%20expenses%20%E2%80%94%20aren't%20subject%20to%20the%20early%20withdrawal%20penalty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20financial%20pros%20who%20spoke%20with%20BI%20say%20that%20taking%20early%20distributions%20is%20generally%20a%20recipe%20for%20disaster%20for%20your%20retirement%20savings%20and%20long-term%20financial%20health%20for%20a%20number%20of%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20the%20advice%20against%20drawing%20on%20your%20retirement%20fund%20early%20comes%20down%20to%20timing.%20Those%20taking%20the%20withdrawals%C2%A0usually%20do%20so%20when%20they're%20still%20working%20or%20in%20a%20year%20in%20which%20they%20have%20worked.%20This%20means%20their%20retirement%20account%20withdrawals%20will%20be%20taxed%20at%20their%20income%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLet's%20say%20you're%20laid%20off%20in%20December%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20have%20made%20your%20income%20for%20the%20entire%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chris%20Chen%2C%20a%20certified%20financial%20planner%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20Insight%20Financial%20Strategists.%20%26quot%3BYou%20often%20end%20up%20taking%20it%20at%20the%20peak%20of%20where%20your%20income%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20the%20early%20withdrawals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20also%20may%20rely%20on%20early%20distributions%20more%20during%20recessions%2C%20when%20there's%20higher%20unemployment.%20That%20means%20they're%20probably%20selling%20their%20holdings%20when%20the%20market%20is%20down%2C%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshould-i-buy-individual-stocks-or-etfs-arnott-research-affiliates-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ERob%20Arnott%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Research%20Affiliates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20get%20a%20triple%20whammy%3A%20You%20lose%20your%20job%2C%20you%20lose%20money%20in%20your%20401(k)%2C%20and%20you%20have%20to%20pay%20a%20tax%20to%20get%20access%20to%20the%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20Arnott%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20and%20perhaps%20most%20importantly%2C%20taking%20early%20withdrawals%20is%20likely%20to%20hurt%20the%20future%20growth%20potential%20of%20your%20money%2C%20said%20Bryan%20Kuderna%2C%20a%20certified%20financial%20planner%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20Kuderna%20Financial%20Team.%20Going%20back%20to%201950%2C%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20has%20averaged%2011.5%25%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Faverage-stock-market-return%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eannual%20returns%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20dividends%20reinvested%2C%20according%20to%20DQYDJ%2C%20an%20investing%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20essentially%20robbing%20themselves%20of%20their%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20Kuderna%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20long-term%20effect%20is%20they're%20reducing%20both%20that%20dollar%20amount%20plus%20the%20decades%20of%20compounded%20interest%20on%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20simple%20fix%20to%20taking%20early%20distributions%3A%20building%20up%20even%20a%20small%20savings%20buffer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKelly%20Hahn%2C%20head%20of%20retirement%20research%20at%20Vanguard%2C%20said%20that%20those%20with%20just%20a%20%242%2C000%20savings%20buffer%20were%20less%20likely%20to%20take%20hardship%20distributions%20and%20cash%20out%20of%20their%20401(k)s%20when%20they%20switched%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20our%20recent%20survey%2C%20we%20found%20that%20having%20an%20emergency%20savings%20was%20the%20single%20most%20important%20factor%20in%20achieving%20financial%20well-being%2C%26quot%3B%20Hahn%20said%20in%20an%20email%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20other%20solutions%20to%20avoid%20taking%20an%20early%20distribution%2C%20Kuderna%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20you%20can%20borrow%20against%20your%20retirement%20account.%20While%20it's%20not%20ideal%20because%20you%20often%20can't%20continue%20contributing%20to%20the%20account%20while%20you%20pay%20the%20loan%20back%2C%20it's%20better%20than%20tapping%20into%20the%20original%20funds.%20That's%20because%20there's%20no%20penalty%2C%20no%20tax%20obligation%2C%20and%20the%20interest%20paid%20goes%20back%20to%20your%20own%20account%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20circumstance%20in%20which%20Kuderna%20allows%20a%20client%20to%20draw%20on%20funds%20from%20a%20retirement%20account%20is%20when%20they%20have%20credit%20card%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20know%20they've%20got%20%2420%2C000%20of%20credit%20card%20debt%20at%2022%25%20interest%2C%20then%20we're%20like%2C%20'Alright%2C%20bite%20the%20bullet%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BNothing%20is%20costing%20as%20much%20as%20that%2020%25%20annual%20loss.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearly-401k-withdrawals-hardship-distributions-retirement-funds-investing-advice-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1753867802000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6888e9b6f748d8c055f67203%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearly-401k-withdrawals-hardship-distributions-retirement-funds-investing-advice-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BThey're%20essentially%20robbing%20themselves%20of%20their%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20financial%20professional%20told%20BI.%20More%20Americans%20are%20drawing%20early%20from%20401(k)s%2C%20Vanguard%20says.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22wedwards%40businessinsider.com%20(William%20Edwards)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearly-401k-withdrawals-hardship-distributions-retirement-funds-investing-advice-2025-7