-news%2Fdog-attack-in-gurugram-pet-husky-attacks-woman-at-gurugram-does-not-let-hand-go-for-15-seconds-8982119%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Older%20job%20seekers%20may%20be%20hurting%20their%20chances%20of%20landing%20a%20job.%20A%20career%20coach%20shares%205%20strategies%20to%20avoid%20self-sabotage.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224356%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Headshot%20of%20Loren%20Greiff%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68893085f748d8c055f67dbf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223267%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EEYT%20PHOTOGRAPHY%20LLC%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELoren%20Greiff%20founded%20a%20career%20coaching%20business%20to%20help%20executives%20over%2040%20with%20their%20next%20steps.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20told%20BI%20that%20she%20has%20five%20strategies%20to%20help%20older%20job%20seekers%20combat%20ageism%20and%20their%20own%20negative%20beliefs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGreiff%20recommended%20showcasing%20value%20over%20quantity%2C%20continual%20learning%2C%20and%20career%20growth.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20age%2054%2C%20executive%20career%20coach%20and%20strategist%20Loren%20Greiff%20worked%20at%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20well-respected%20executive%20search%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20experience%20as%20an%20older%20worker%20inspired%20Greiff%2C%20who's%20based%20in%20Asheville%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20to%20found%20her%20own%20career%20coaching%20business%20%E2%80%94%20PortfolioRocket%20%E2%80%94%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreiff%2C%20now%2061%2C%20aims%20to%20help%20executives%20over%2040%20take%20their%20next%20career%20step%20and%20avoid%20being%20put%20out%20to%20pasture.%20Since%20launching%20her%20business%2C%20Greiff%20has%20helped%20candidates%20land%20jobs%20at%20companies%20such%20as%20Meta%2C%20Target%2C%20Ford%2C%20and%20Dick's%20Sporting%20Goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bd10c080-6e9c-4a42-a164-3986ca717844%5C%22%3EAgeism%20within%20organizations%20isn't%20the%20only%20problem%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20with%20older%20employees%20over%20the%20past%20four%20years%2C%20Greiff%20told%20BI%20the%20problem%20isn't%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbias-against-older-and-younger-workers-bad-for-business-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eageism%20in%20organizations%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20negative%20beliefs%20held%20by%20the%20candidates%20themselves%20may%20keep%20them%20from%20reaching%20their%20career%20potential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20belief%20%E2%80%94%20and%20also%20the%20biggest%20lie%20%E2%80%94%20is%20that%20they're%20powerless%20against%20ageism%2C%26quot%3B%20Greiff%20said.%20Acknowledging%20the%20bias%20exists%20does%20not%20mean%20candidates%20don't%20have%20the%20agency%20to%20overcome%20it%2C%20the%20coach%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Greiff%2C%20the%20second%20mistake%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-americans-silent-generation-working-longer-retirement-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eolder%20job%20seekers%3C%2Fa%3E%20make%20is%20believing%20buzzwords%20hiring%20managers%20may%20use%2C%20like%20%26quot%3Boverqualified%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Btoo%20expensive%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bnot%20a%20culture%20fit.%26quot%3B%20Instead%2C%20she%20said%2C%20words%20like%20these%20may%20mask%20biases%20or%20deeper%20systemic%20issues%20in%20the%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20making%20her%20own%20job%20transition%20as%20an%20older%20candidate%20and%20guiding%20others%20in%20this%20age%20group%20through%20theirs%2C%20Greiff%20has%20devised%20job-search%20strategies%20that%20help%20over-40s%20combat%20negative%20thought%20patterns%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshocked-when-recruiter-said-too-old-tech-job-ageism-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edirect%20ageism%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20applications%20and%20interviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20emphasized%20that%20older%20employees%20need%20to%20repackage%20their%20deep%20work%20experience%2C%20using%20these%20five%20strategies%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223555ba80-46d3-4520-a848-b3241d0c8c86%5C%22%3E1.%20Accept%20that%20added%20years%20of%20experience%20don't%20automatically%20add%20up%20to%20added%20value%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGreiff%20shared%20that%20many%20older%20candidates%20she's%20coached%20assume%20that%20work%20experience%20and%20career%20relevance%20are%20one%20and%20the%20same.%20But%20she%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-struggling-tech-jobs-applying-junior-roles-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etwo%20decades%20of%20experience%3C%2Fa%3E%20might%20be%20worth%20less%20to%20employers%20than%20someone%20else's%20two%20years%20if%20a%20candidate%20can't%20show%20they've%20been%20building%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BExperience%20is%20time%3B%20relevance%20speaks%20to%20the%20impact%20to%20lead%20and%20drive%20for%20now%20and%20what's%20next%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDecision%20makers%20seek%20agility%20and%20willingness%20to%20learn%20outside%20of%20what%20you%20already%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20Greiff%20added%2C%20saying%20candidates%20shouldn't%20rely%20on%20their%20time%20in%20a%20role%20to%20speak%20for%20itself.%20%26quot%3BStart%20addressing%20the%20underlying%20issues%20decision%20makers%20are%20concerned%20about%20most.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229a2b9e5a-220c-4192-a484-6c20774c7507%5C%22%3E2.%20Stop%20referring%20to%20all%20of%20your%20experience%20in%20the%20past%20tense%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Greiff%2C%20decision%20makers%20aren't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-quietly-search-for-your-next-job-on-linkedin-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Escrolling%20LinkedIn%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20verify%2