20of%20them%2C%20especially%20those%20with%20lower%20incomes%2C%20are%20getting%20married%20or%20living%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdating-nightmare-tea-whisper-network-apps-save-us-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eromantic%20partners%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20men%20struggle%20economically%2C%20fewer%20women%20are%20as%20interested%20in%20marrying%20or%20having%20kids%20with%20them.%20A%20third%20of%20US%20adults%20over%2050%20say%20they're%20childless%20because%20they%20never%20found%20the%20right%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20conversations%20Americans%20are%20having%20about%20starting%20a%20family%20or%20having%20another%20kid%20are%20%26quot%3Bvery%20layered%2C%26quot%3B%20Paige%20Connell%2C%20a%20mother%20of%20four%20and%20parenting%20influencer%2C%20tells%20me.%20She%20hears%20from%20mothers%20who%20feel%20burned%20out%20working%20and%20caring%20for%20their%20kids%2C%20and%20worry%20that%20having%20another%20would%20overwhelm%20them%20or%20hurt%20their%20careers.%20She%20also%20hears%20from%20childless%20people%20who%20don't%20know%20how%20they%20could%20afford%20childcare%20or%20a%20bigger%20home.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-spend-45-income-afford-a-home-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAffordability%20is%20the%20biggest%20concern%3C%2Fa%3E%20she%20hears%20from%20parents%20and%20people%20considering%20having%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-prices-record-high-sales-real-estate-mortgage-rates-nar-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHousing%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20the%20single%20biggest%20factor%20preventing%20Americans%20from%20having%20as%20many%20kids%20as%20they%20want%2C%20according%20to%20a%20recent%20report%20published%20by%20the%20Institute%20for%20Family%20Studies%2C%20a%20conservative%20think%20tank.%20In%20IFS's%20recent%20survey%20of%20more%20than%208%2C000%20Americans%2018%20to%2054%20years%20old%2C%20a%20quarter%20of%20respondents%20listed%20housing%20costs%20as%20a%20concern%2C%20while%2030%25%20cited%20the%20cost%20of%20childcare%2C%20and%2026%25%20said%20they%20wanted%20more%20leisure%20time.%20But%20of%20those%20factors%2C%20housing%20costs%20had%20the%20largest%20total%20effect%20on%20family%20size.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHousing%20is%20the%20biggest%20affordability%20hurdle%20facing%20families%2C%26quot%3B%20Lyman%20Stone%2C%20a%20co-author%20of%20the%20report%20and%20the%20director%20of%20IFS's%20Pronatalism%20Initiative%2C%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20thing%20that%20everybody%20thinks%20about%20first%2C%20as%20soon%20as%20they're%20thinking%20about%20fertility.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Connell's%20case%2C%20being%20able%20to%20afford%20her%20three-bedroom%20home%20has%20allowed%20her%20to%20have%20the%20number%20of%20kids%20she%20wanted%2C%20she%20says.%20She's%20among%20the%20lucky%20millennial%20homeowners%20who%20landed%20a%203%25%20mortgage%20interest%20rate%20on%20her%20suburban%20Boston%20house%20back%20in%202020.%20If%20housing%20costs%20had%20been%20as%20high%20then%20as%20they%20are%20now%2C%20she%20doesn't%20think%20she%20and%20her%20husband%20would%20have%20had%20a%20fourth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20growing%20conversation%20about%20not%20having%20children%20unless%20you%2C%20quote%20unquote%2C%20have%20enough%20space%20for%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BLike%2C%20if%20you%20can't%20afford%20to%20give%20them%20their%20own%20bedroom%2C%20then%20you%20should%20have%20shouldn't%20have%20that%20child.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStone's%20research%20has%20found%20that%20the%20problem%20isn't%20just%20the%20cost%20of%20housing%2C%20it's%20the%20scarcity%20of%20the%20types%20of%20homes%20most%20appealing%20to%20families%3A%20those%20with%20two%20or%20more%20bedrooms%20in%20communities%20that%20are%20safe%2C%20walkable%2C%20and%20have%20decent%20schools.%20People%20who%20have%20kids%20or%20want%20families%20tend%20to%20prefer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-home-sales-inventory-prices-mortgage-rates-economy-redfin-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esingle-family%20homes%20over%20apartments%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Above%20all%2C%20they%20just%20want%20room%20to%20grow.%20%26quot%3BIt%20really%20is%20the%20case%20that%20if%20you%20give%20people%20more%20bedrooms%20in%20their%20apartments%2C%20they're%20more%20interested%20in%20having%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20Stone%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fundamental%20driver%20of%20soaring%20rent%20and%20mortgage%20prices%20is%20a%20steep%20housing%20shortage.%20Family-sized%20housing%20is%20particularly%20scarce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20rents%20rise%2C%20single%20adults%20can%20live%20with%20housemates%20to%20split%20costs%2C%20says%20Emily%20Hamilton%2C%20a%20housing%20researcher%20at%20the%20libertarian-leaning%20Mercatus%20Center%20at%20George%20Mason%20University.%20People%20with%20kids%20aren't%20likely%20to%20do%20the%20same%2C%20meaning%20they%20can't%20as%20easily%20defray%20rising%20housing%20costs.%20A%20group%20of%20roommates%20%26quot%3Bcan%20generally%20pay%20more%20for%20housing%20than%20one%20or%20two%20working%20parents%20with%20kids%20could%2C%26quot%3B%20Hamilton%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDevelopers%20also%20aren't%20incentivized%20to%20build%20affordable%20family-sized%20housing%2C%20especially%20in%20expensive%20cities.%20They%20tend%20to%20build%20two%20more%20profitable%20types%20of%20homes%3A%20detached%20single-family%20houses%20with%20lots%20of%20lawn%20and%20square%20footage%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20cities%2C%20and%20large%20apartment%20buildings%20with%20cramped%20one-bedroom%20and%20studio%20units%20in%20the%20urban%20core.%20Neither%20make%20for%20affordable%20homes%20for%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20in%20large%20part%20because%20land-use%20regulations%2C%20building%20codes%2C%20and%20financing%20models%20have%20made%20it%20very%20difficult%20or%20impossible%20to%20build%20anything%20in%20between%2C%20Michael%20Eliason%2C%20a%20Seattle-based%20architect%20and%20founder%20of%20Larch%20Lab%2C%20tells%20me.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-now-good-time-to-buy-home-real-estate-agents-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAffordable%20housing%20designed%20for%20families%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20increasingly%20relegated%20to%20far-flung%20exurbs%20and%20rural%20areas.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20hit%20the%20limits%20of%20sprawl%2C%26quot%3B%20Eliason%20says.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20we%20%26quot%3Baren't%20good%20at%20building%20urban%2C%20multi-family%20housing%20that%20is%20of%20a%20quality%20similar%20to%20living%20in%20a%20detached%20house%20or%20a%20townhouse.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBobby%20Fijan%2C%20a%20real%20estate%20developer%20who's%20been%20pushing%20for%20more%20family-centric%20dense%20housing%2C%20tells%20me%20there's%20a%20lot%20developers%20could%20do%20under%20the%20current%20constraints%20to%20make%20their%20buildings%20more%20family-friendly.%20That%20could%20include%20designing%20two-bedroom%20apartments%20for%20a%20couple%20and%20a%20child%2C%20rather%20than%20two%20roommates%2C%20by%20featuring%20just%20one%20bathroom%20and%20reallocating%20square%20footage%20to%20an%20additional%20bedroom.%20Or%20apartment%20buildings%20could%20include%20a%20children's%20playroom%20in%20their%20common%20space%20instead%20of%20a%20dog%20washing%20station.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20Vice%20President%20JD%20Vance%20talk%20openly%20about%20their%20concerns%20with%20the%20falling%20birth%20rate.%20Vance%20has%20famously%20blamed%20society's%20ills%20on%20%26quot%3Bchildless%20cat%20ladies%2C%26quot%3B%20while%20Trump%20has%20promised%20to%20usher%20in%20a%20baby%20boom.%20Their%20pro-natalist%20policies%20are%20focused%20on%20expanding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjd-vance-expanded-child-tax-credit-proposal-pro-family-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20cash%20benefits%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20parents%2C%20including%20Trump's%20proposal%20for%20a%20%245%2C000%20baby%20bonus.%20But%20they've%20also%20talked%20about%20opening%20up%20federal%20land%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-freedom-cities-housing-costs-nevada-las-vegas-plan-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehousing%20construction%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyimbys-harris-housing-policy-walz-lower-home-prices-affordability-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDemocrats%20have%20gotten%20behind%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20idea%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrad%20Wilcox%2C%20cofounder%20of%20IFS%2C%20previously%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20group%20has%20had%20conversations%20with%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20Domestic%20Policy%20Council%20about%20pronatalist%20policies.%20He%20pointed%20to%20the%20administration's%20efforts%20to%20sell%20federal%20land%20for%20housing%20construction%20as%20a%20promising%20path%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20their%20%26quot%3Bbig%20beautiful%20bill%2C%26quot%3B%20Republican%20lawmakers%20expanded%20the%20child%20tax%20credit%20from%20%242%2C000%20per%20kid%20to%20%242%2C200.%20The%20proposal%20excludes%20the%20neediest%20families%20who%20don't%20make%20enough%20money%20to%20be%20eligible%20for%20the%20full%20benefit.%20The%20reconciliation%20package%20also%20includes%20a%20baby%20bonus%20in%20the%20form%20of%20investment%20accounts%20with%20%241%2C000%20of%20seed%20funds%20for%20every%20American%20baby%20born%20from%202025%20through%202028.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20researchers%2C%20including%20Stone%2C%20have%20found%20that%20an%20expanded%20child%20tax%20credit%20would%20increase%20birth%20rates%2C%20it%20wouldn't%20be%20enough%20for%20many%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECatherine%2C%20a%2043-year-old%20physician%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsan-francisco-investment-properties-real-estate-rebound-rents-multifamily-fortress-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESan%20Francisco%20Bay%20Area%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20a%20neuroscientist%2C%20make%20about%20%24500%2C000%20a%20year%20combined.%20But%20the%20couple%20and%20their%20two%20young%20daughters%20live%20in%20one%20of%20the%20most%20expensive%20housing%20markets%20in%20the%20country%20and%20bought%20their%20three-bedroom%20house%20in%20Carmel%20for%20nearly%20%241.7%20million%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20their%201%2C700-square-foot%20home%20has%20enough%20space%20for%20a%20third%20baby%2C%20Catherine%20worries%20that%20expanding%20their%20family%20would%20deplete%20their%20financial%20safety%20net%20and%20make%20their%20fixed%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20mostly%20their%20mortgage%20%E2%80%94%20unaffordable.%20If%20either%20she%20or%20her%20husband%20takes%20a%20step%20back%20at%20work%20to%20help%20take%20care%20of%20a%20third%20baby%2C%20they'd%20likely%20struggle%20with%20their%20sky-high%20mortgage%20payments.%20She%20asked%20that%20her%20last%20name%20be%20excluded%20from%20the%20story%20because%20she%20fears%20her%20employer%20would%20discriminate%20against%20her%20if%20they%20knew%20she%20was%20considering%20having%20a%20third%20kid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20us%2C%20it's%20not%20so%20much%20maternity%20and%20paternity%20leave%20guarantees%20that%20would%20lead%20us%20to%20have%20a%20third%20child%2C%20it's%20really%20about%20reducing%20that%20fixed%20cost%20long%20term%2C%26quot%3B%20Catherine%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20doing%20OK%20now%2C%20but%20if%20we%20add%20this%20third%20element%20and%20something%20else%20happens%2C%20how%20are%20we%20going%20to%20pay%20our%20bills%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoving%20doesn't%20make%20sense%20for%20them.%20A%20cheaper%20three-bedroom%20home%20is%20nearly%20impossible%20to%20come%20by%20in%20their%20school%20district.%20And%20Catherine's%20job%2C%20which%20requires%20her%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office%20five%20days%20a%20week%2C%20means%20they%20can't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstates-more-affordable-for-single-homebuyers-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edecamp%20to%20a%20cheaper%20state%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20she%20or%20her%20husband%20were%20to%20lose%20their%20jobs%20or%20want%20to%20find%20other%20work%2C%20the%20opportunities%20in%20their%20niche%20fields%20are%20much%20more%20abundant%20in%20the%20Bay%20Area%20than%20they%20are%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20to%20mention%2C%20they%20love%20living%20in%20Carmel.%20There%20are%20robotics%20and%20surfing%20camps%2C%20a%20plethora%20of%20museums%2C%20and%20access%20to%20the%20outdoors%20%E2%80%94%20all%20great%20for%20raising%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20paying%20for%20the%20neighborhood%2C%20for%20the%20school%20options%2C%20for%20the%20safety%2C%20for%20our%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20Catherine%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Bay%20Area%20is%20just%20really%2C%20really%2C%20really%20expensive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Feliza-relman%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EEliza%20Relman%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20policy%20correspondent%20focused%20on%20housing%2C%20transportation%2C%20and%20infrastructure%20on%20Insider's%20economy%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-baby-boom-housing-boom-home-price-affordability-parenting-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1753862881000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F685da4903d5881a51c1c2cb3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-baby-boom-housing-boom-home-price-affordability-parenting-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20America%20wants%20to%20increase%20its%